Title : Taleomey River
Text : The '''Taleomey River''' is a [[river]] in the northernmost [[Pacific Ranges]] of the [[Coast Mountains]] in the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast region]] of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]], flowing west to  [[South Bentinck Arm]] where its waters enter the sea a few miles north of the head of that inlet.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/17593.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Taleomey River"]</ref>  The [[Asseek River]] also enters the head of South Bentinck Arm, flowing into its head from the south.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/25996.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Asseek River"]</ref>

Immediately north of the Taleomey estuary, the [[Noeick River]] also enters South Bentinck Arm.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/16970.html BC Names/GeoBC "Noeick River"]</ref>  On the north side of that river's mouth is the locality of [[South Bentinck]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/40872.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "South Bentinck (locality)"]</ref>

[[Taleomy Indian Reserve No. 3]], which is governed by the [[Nuxalk Nation]], is located at the mouth of the Taleomey River.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/64994.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Taleomy 3 (Indian reserve)"]</ref>  South Bentinck Arm is narrowed offshore from the estuary of the river by '''Taleomey Narrows'''.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/40897.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Taleomey Narrows"]</ref>

